{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "WH-Question Formation speaking drill (Jeopardy-style)",
  "description": "Add a new speaking drill where the app presents a short answer statement (e.g., 'She left at 7 a.m. because she had a meeting') and the learner must speak the WH-question that would elicit it (e.g., 'Why did she leave at 7 a.m.?' or 'What time did she leave?'). This targets a real weakness for learners — forming correct auxiliary/word-order in questions — and combines listening (TTS of the answer) with speaking (speech recognition) plus LLM grading.\n\nBackend:\n- New router `app/routers/wh_questions.py` with two endpoints:\n  * `POST /api/wh-questions/start` → returns a batch of 5 items. Each item has `id`, `answer_sentence` (the statement), `target_wh` (one of who/what/when/where/why/how — the expected question word), and optional `hint`. Generate via Copilot with a strict JSON prompt; fall back to a small built-in seed list on LLM failure.\n  * `POST /api/wh-questions/grade` with body `{item_id, answer_sentence, target_wh, user_question}`. Calls Copilot to judge: correctness (bool), wh_word_matches (bool), grammar_ok (bool), feedback (short string), corrected (string). Persists result to a new `wh_question_attempts` table.\n- New DAL `app/dal/wh_questions.py` with `record_attempt(user_id, target_wh, is_correct, grammar_ok)` and `get_recent_stats(user_id, limit=30)` returning accuracy per wh-word.\n- Schema addition in `app/database.py` SCHEMA and `_MIGRATIONS`:\n  * `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS wh_question_attempts (id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT, user_id TEXT NOT NULL, target_wh TEXT NOT NULL, is_correct INTEGER NOT NULL, grammar_ok INTEGER NOT NULL, created_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now')))`\n  * Since this is a brand-new table, `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS` is sufficient and no `ALTER TABLE` migration is needed (add the CREATE statement to both SCHEMA and as an idempotent entry; no column additions to existing tables).\n- Register router in `app/main.py`.\n\nFrontend:\n- New page `frontend/src/pages/WhQuestionDrill.tsx` with flow: fetch batch → for each item, TTS-speak the answer sentence and show it as text → mic button starts SpeechRecognition → on transcript submit, call grade endpoint → show ✓/✗ with corrected question and short feedback → Next button. After 5 items show a summary with per-wh accuracy bars and a 'Retry missed' button that filters to incorrect items.\n- Add route in `App.tsx` and a launch card on `Home.tsx` in the speaking-drills section (reuse existing card styling).\n- Add `whQuestions` API helpers in `frontend/src/api.ts` (startDrill, grade).\n\nTesting: add `tests/unit/test_wh_questions_dal.py` covering record_attempt + get_recent_stats, and extend an integration test hitting the grade endpoint with a mocked copilot_client.",
