  "description": "Add a new 'Minimal Pairs' drill that trains learners to hear subtle phoneme contrasts (e.g., /ɪ/ vs /iː/ in ship/sheep, /æ/ vs /e/ in bat/bet, /l/ vs /r/ in light/right, /b/ vs /v/ in berry/very). Each round: backend synthesizes TTS audio of ONE word from a pair; the user hears audio and taps which of the two displayed words they heard. Tracks accuracy per phoneme-contrast pair so learners can see their weakest contrasts. This is a high-value listening skill not yet covered by the recent drill wave.\n\nBackend (`app/routers/minimal_pairs.py` new): \n- Curated static list (no LLM needed) of ~40 pair items grouped by contrast category (e.g., IY_vs_IH, AE_vs_EH, L_vs_R, B_vs_V, S_vs_SH, TH_vs_S, N_vs_NG). Define in module-level constant `MINIMAL_PAIRS` with fields {id, contrast, word_a, word_b, example_a, example_b}.\n- GET `/api/minimal-pairs/session?contrast=optional&count=8` → returns a randomized session: list of items where each item includes {item_id, contrast, word_a, word_b, target: 'a'|'b' (which one audio plays), audio_b64} using existing TTS helper (reuse pattern from `app/routers/listening.py` or `shadowing.py`). Keep `target` server-authoritative.\n- POST `/api/minimal-pairs/answer` with body {item_id, contrast, target, chosen} → records to new table `minimal_pairs_attempts(id INTEGER PK AUTOINCREMENT, created_at TEXT NOT NULL, contrast TEXT NOT NULL, item_id TEXT NOT NULL, target TEXT NOT NULL, chosen TEXT NOT NULL, correct INTEGER NOT NULL)`. Return {correct: bool, streak: int}.\n- GET `/api/minimal-pairs/stats` → aggregates per-contrast accuracy over last 30 days: [{contrast, attempts, correct, accuracy}].\n- DAL in `app/dal/minimal_pairs.py`: `record_attempt`, `get_contrast_stats`, `get_weakest_contrasts`.\n\nDatabase (`app/database.py`): add the `minimal_pairs_attempts` CREATE TABLE to SCHEMA, AND add to `_MIGRATIONS` the statement `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS minimal_pairs_attempts (id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT, created_at TEXT NOT NULL, contrast TEXT NOT NULL, item_id TEXT NOT NULL, target TEXT NOT NULL, chosen TEXT NOT NULL, correct INTEGER NOT NULL)` so existing DBs pick it up.\n\nFrontend (`frontend/src/pages/MinimalPairsPage.tsx` new + route entry in `frontend/src/App.tsx` and a Home card): \n- Phase 1 (select): optional contrast filter dropdown + 'Start' button (defaults to mixed).\n- Phase 2 (drill): large play/replay audio button, two big word-choice buttons side-by-side, after selection show correct/incorrect flash + a short 'example sentence' for the word actually played, then auto-advance.\n- Phase 3 (summary): overall accuracy, per-contrast breakdown bar, 'Weakest contrast' callout linking to retry with that contrast filter, Retry / Home buttons. Dark-mode + mobile responsive consistent with existing drills.\n- Register router in `app/main.py`.\n\nTesting: unit tests for DAL aggregation and an integration test hitting `/api/minimal-pairs/session` and POST `/answer` with both correct/incorrect paths in `tests/unit/test_minimal_pairs.py`.",
