{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "Preposition Cloze Drill — fill-in preposition practice with contextual feedback",
  "description": "Add a short, focused drill where learners fill in the missing preposition (in/on/at/for/to/of/with/by/from/about/over/under, etc.) in natural sentences. Helps address one of the most persistent EFL error categories. Flow: user taps 'Preposition Drill' on Home → gets 8 sentences one at a time, each with a blank ('I'm good ___ math.') and a small chip-row of 4–6 preposition options (correct answer + plausible distractors). On select: instant ✓/✗ feedback, one-line explanation of why (e.g., 'good at + skill'), and a 'Say it aloud' mic button that uses existing pronunciation scoring on the full completed sentence to reinforce collocation memory. End-of-session summary shows accuracy, top confused pairs (e.g., in↔on), and a 'retry missed' button.\n\nBackend (app/routers/prepositions.py, new): GET /api/prepositions/session?count=8&level=beginner|intermediate returns list of {id, sentence_with_blank, options, answer, explanation, category}. Items sourced from a curated JSON seed (app/data/prepositions.json, ~60 items across time/place/collocation/phrasal categories) — no LLM call needed for v1, keeps latency <50ms. POST /api/prepositions/attempt {item_id, chosen, correct, response_ms} logs to new table preposition_attempts. GET /api/prepositions/stats returns recent accuracy + top 3 confused pairs.\n\nSchema (app/database.py SCHEMA + _MIGRATIONS):\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS preposition_attempts (id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT, item_id TEXT NOT NULL, chosen TEXT NOT NULL, correct TEXT NOT NULL, is_correct INTEGER NOT NULL, category TEXT, response_ms INTEGER, created_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now')));\n\nMigration (append to _MIGRATIONS so existing DBs get it):\n\"CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS preposition_attempts (id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT, item_id TEXT NOT NULL, chosen TEXT NOT NULL, correct TEXT NOT NULL, is_correct INTEGER NOT NULL, category TEXT, response_ms INTEGER, created_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now')))\"\n\nDAL: app/dal/prepositions.py with load_items(), record_attempt(), get_recent_stats(), get_confused_pairs().\n\nFrontend: new React page frontend/src/pages/PrepositionDrill.tsx + route entry in App.tsx + Home card link. Reuse existing card/chip/feedback styling from QuickGrammar/ErrorCorrection pages. Mic integration via existing pronunciation hook.\n\nRegister router in app/main.py.",
  "rationale": "Prepositions are a top-3 EFL error category and currently unaddressed in the app. Pattern mirrors existing successful drills (error_correction, tag_questions, wh_questions) so implementation risk is low. Seed-data approach keeps it fast/deterministic and testable. Adds real user-facing UI (card on Home + full drill page + summary) — not a backend-only feature.",
  "files_to_change": [
