{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "Pause & Predict listening drill (predict next chunk from audio)",
  "description": "Add a new listening drill called 'Pause & Predict' that trains predictive processing — a core skill for real-time listening comprehension. The app plays a sentence via TTS and cuts off just before the final 1–3 word chunk. The user must type (or optionally speak) what they think completes the sentence. After submitting, the app reveals the true completion, plays the full sentence, and scores the answer using case-insensitive normalized match plus a lenient semantic/synonym check (e.g., 'the store' ≈ 'a store', 'happy' ≈ 'glad'). This differs from existing drills: Sentence Echo = repeat verbatim, Listen & Summarize = gist, Dictation = full transcription. Pause & Predict specifically practices TOP-DOWN prediction from context.\n\nImplementation:\n1) New router app/routers/pause_predict.py with endpoints:\n   - GET /api/pause-predict/session?difficulty=beginner|intermediate|advanced&count=5 → returns list of items {id, full_sentence, prefix_text, expected_completion, alternatives: [str], context_hint, audio_prefix_url, audio_full_url}. Items generated via copilot_client with prompt in app/prompts.py (new PAUSE_PREDICT_PROMPT) producing natural everyday sentences where the final chunk is strongly predictable from context (but not trivial). Cache per (difficulty, date) like other drills.\n   - POST /api/pause-predict/submit with {item_id, user_answer, session_id} → returns {is_correct, is_close, expected, user_answer_normalized, feedback, score}. Scoring: exact match=1.0, alternative match=0.9, semantic-close (LLM judge)=0.6, wrong=0.\n   - POST /api/pause-predict/session/complete → persists summary to new table pause_predict_sessions(id, user_id, difficulty, total, correct, close, avg_score, created_at).\n2) New DAL app/dal/pause_predict.py for session persistence.\n3) Database migration: add to _MIGRATIONS in app/database.py:\n   - \"CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS pause_predict_sessions (id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT, user_id INTEGER, difficulty TEXT NOT NULL, total INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0, correct INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0, close INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0, avg_score REAL NOT NULL DEFAULT 0, created_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now')))\"\n   (New table only; no ALTER needed.) Also register the router in app/main.py.\n4) Frontend: new page frontend/src/pages/PausePredictPage.tsx with flow: Select difficulty → Listen (auto-plays prefix audio, user can replay up to 3x) → type completion → submit → see reveal with full audio playback and per-item feedback → next item → final summary with accuracy, close-match rate, and a 'Replay missed items' button. Add route in frontend/src/App.tsx and a card on the Home page under listening drills (use existing drill card pattern). Include keyboard shortcut: Space=replay, Enter=submit, N=next. Mobile-friendly; supports dark mode using existing tokens.\n\nWhy high value: fills a real gap — none of the existing drills train anticipation/prediction, which is what separates intermediate from fluent listeners. It's short (5 items ≈ 3 min), repeatable daily, and produces measurable progress (prediction accuracy trend).",
