{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "Intonation Arrow Drill — rising vs falling final intonation",
  "description": "Add a new listening micro-drill that trains perception of English sentence-final intonation (a gap in the current prosody tool set — we have stress_spotlight, contrastive_stress, shadowing, and speed_ladder, but nothing that isolates pitch contour). Each question plays a short TTS utterance (5–12 words) and the learner taps one of three chips: ↗ Rising, ↘ Falling, or ↗↘ Rise-Fall. The drill set mixes canonical patterns: yes/no questions and listing-continuations (rising), statements and wh-questions (falling), tag questions asking real info (rising) vs confirming (falling), and exclamations / choice questions (rise-fall).\n\nBackend (`app/routers/intonation_arrow.py`): POST `/api/intonation-arrow/session` returns 8 items from a curated JSON pool under `app/data/intonation_arrow.json` (fields: id, text, pattern ∈ {rising,falling,rise_fall}, explanation, category). POST `/api/intonation-arrow/attempt` with {item_id, chosen, correct, latency_ms} logs to new table `intonation_arrow_attempts(id, item_id, chosen, correct, latency_ms, created_at)`. GET `/api/intonation-arrow/stats` returns accuracy by pattern for the dashboard. TTS reuses existing `/api/tts` endpoint.\n\nFrontend (`frontend/src/pages/IntonationArrowPage.tsx` + route in `App.tsx` + Home card tile): a Listen button (auto-plays once, replay allowed twice), three large arrow chips with aria-labels, immediate correct/incorrect feedback showing the target contour and a one-line explanation (\"Yes/No questions typically rise at the end\"), and an end-of-session summary with per-pattern accuracy and a Retry Wrong Only button.\n\nMigration required — add to `_MIGRATIONS` in `app/database.py`:\n`CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS intonation_arrow_attempts (id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT, item_id TEXT NOT NULL, chosen TEXT NOT NULL, correct INTEGER NOT NULL, latency_ms INTEGER, created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP);`\nand `CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_intonation_arrow_created ON intonation_arrow_attempts(created_at);`\n\nRationale: intonation perception is a well-known weakness for Japanese learners (flatter L1 contour) and directly affects listening comprehension of questions vs statements and speaking naturalness. Complements existing stress/rhythm drills without overlap.",
  "files_to_modify": [
    "app/routers/intonation_arrow.py",
    "app/data/intonation_arrow.json",
    "app/database.py",
    "app/main.py",
    "frontend/src/pages/IntonationArrowPage.tsx"
  ],
  "priority": "high",
  "estimated_complexity": "medium"
}
