{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "Collocation Chef: verb+noun collocation drill (make/do/take/have/give)",
  "description": "Add a new drill that targets collocations — one of the biggest fluency gaps not yet covered (all recent features were perception/grammar/pronunciation). Learners frequently make errors like 'do a decision' instead of 'make a decision'. This feature presents short English sentences with a blank before a noun phrase, and the learner selects the correct delexical/light verb from a chip set (make, do, take, have, give, pay, keep, break, etc.). After each answer, a brief explanation + 1–2 related collocations are shown to reinforce the lexical chunk.\n\n### Backend\n- New router `app/routers/collocations.py` with endpoints:\n  - `GET /api/collocations/session?count=8&difficulty=easy|medium|hard` — returns a session of items `{id, sentence_before, sentence_after, noun_phrase, correct_verb, verb_choices:[...4], hint, related_collocations:[...]}`. Source items from a seed list (hard-coded Python list of ~60 curated items across difficulties) plus optional Copilot-generated items via existing `copilot_client` when seed is exhausted (pattern: like `intonation_arrow.py`). Keep it deterministic with seed list first for reliability.\n  - `POST /api/collocations/attempt` — body `{item_id, sentence, correct_verb, chosen_verb, is_correct, response_ms}` → persists to new table.\n  - `GET /api/collocations/stats` — returns `{total_attempts, accuracy, per_verb_accuracy:{make:0.8,...}, weakest_verbs:[...], recent_sessions:[...]}` for progress visualization.\n\n### DB (new table — include migration)\nAdd to `SCHEMA` in `app/database.py`:\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS collocation_attempts (\n  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n  item_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n  sentence TEXT NOT NULL,\n  correct_verb TEXT NOT NULL,\n  chosen_verb TEXT NOT NULL,\n  is_correct INTEGER NOT NULL,\n  response_ms INTEGER,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now'))\n);\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_colloc_created ON collocation_attempts(created_at);\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_colloc_verb ON collocation_attempts(correct_verb);\n```\nSince this is a brand-new table, `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS` is sufficient (no ALTER needed because the table doesn't exist in any prior version). Also append a no-op marker migration string to `_MIGRATIONS` like `\"CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS collocation_attempts (id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT, item_id TEXT NOT NULL, sentence TEXT NOT NULL, correct_verb TEXT NOT NULL, chosen_verb TEXT NOT NULL, is_correct INTEGER NOT NULL, response_ms INTEGER, created_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now')))\"` to guarantee the table exists on already-initialized DBs.\n\n### DAL\nNew `app/dal/collocations.py` with `save_attempt(...)`, `get_stats(days:int=30)`, `get_per_verb_accuracy()`.\n\n### Frontend\nNew page `frontend/src/pages/CollocationChef.tsx` + route entry + home-page card link. UI flow:\n1. Difficulty selector → Start.\n2. Per item: show sentence with blank highlighted, 4 verb chips, click to answer. Instant feedback: green/red, reveal correct verb, show 1–2 related collocations (e.g., 'make a mistake', 'make progress').\n3. Progress bar, timer per item (captures response_ms).\n4. Summary screen: accuracy, per-verb breakdown bar chart, weakest verb call-out, retry / next session buttons.\n5. Add a small 'Per-verb accuracy' mini-card visible in the summary fed from `/stats`.\n\nSupport dark mode, keyboard shortcuts (1–4 to pick a chip), and mobile layout consistent with other drills.\n\n### Why this feature\nCollocations are repeatedly called out in SLA research as a top predictor of perceived fluency, and none of iterations 695–704 addressed lexical chunking. It complements the existing grammar/pronunciation drills with a vocabulary-in-context angle, and the per-verb accuracy visualization adds concrete learning-progress feedback (matching the app's listening/speaking goal of user-facing progress UI).",
  "files_to_modify": [
    "app/routers/collocations.py",
    "app/dal/collocations.py",
    "app/database.py",
    "app/main.py",
    "frontend/src/pages/CollocationChef.tsx"
  ],
  "priority": "medium",
  "estimated_complexity": "medium"
}
