{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "Elastic Sentence drill: progressive expansion + speak to build utterance length",
  "description": "Add a new Listening+Speaking drill that trains working memory and fluency by progressively expanding a target sentence. UX flow: (1) User picks a difficulty (short/medium/long target, e.g. 6/10/14 words). (2) Backend generates a target sentence plus an expansion chain via Copilot, e.g. target 'I would like some coffee with milk please' → chain ['coffee', 'some coffee', 'like some coffee', \"I'd like some coffee\", \"I'd like some coffee with milk\", \"I'd like some coffee with milk please\"]. Each chain step adds 1-3 tokens building toward the target. (3) Frontend plays each chunk via existing TTS (reuse /api/pronunciation/tts or shared util), user repeats after each step (optional mic via Web Speech API for transcript match), and a growing 'sentence builder' visualization shows new words highlighted as they are added. (4) Final step: user speaks the full target; transcript is matched with normalized token overlap (reuse logic from app/routers/shadowing.py or paraphrase.py scoring). (5) Result screen shows chain length reached, final-utterance accuracy %, and a 'longest successfully spoken utterance (words)' stat.\n\nBackend: new router app/routers/elastic_sentence.py with POST /api/elastic-sentence/generate (difficulty -> {target, chain[]}) using Copilot prompt added to app/prompts.py (ELASTIC_SENTENCE_PROMPT), and POST /api/elastic-sentence/submit persisting a session row. Register router in app/main.py. DAL: app/dal/elastic_sentence.py with create_session(user_id, target, chain_len, max_reached, accuracy) and recent_sessions(user_id, limit). Schema: add table elastic_sentence_sessions(id INTEGER PK, user_id INTEGER, target TEXT, chain_length INTEGER, max_step_reached INTEGER, final_accuracy REAL, created_at TEXT) in app/database.py SCHEMA, and add migration to _MIGRATIONS: `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS elastic_sentence_sessions (id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT, user_id INTEGER NOT NULL, target TEXT NOT NULL, chain_length INTEGER NOT NULL, max_step_reached INTEGER NOT NULL, final_accuracy REAL NOT NULL, created_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP)` (CREATE TABLE form is acceptable for new tables since the table does not yet exist).\n\nFrontend: new page frontend/src/pages/ElasticSentencePage.tsx with difficulty picker, chain playback stepper, per-step 'play/repeat/next' controls, final-speak step with transcript diff highlight, and results card showing max_step_reached / chain_length and final_accuracy. Add route + home-card entry link. Reuse TTS hook and transcript utilities already in frontend.\n\nWhy: differentiates from recent drills (Shadowing, Paraphrase, Pause & Predict) by explicitly training utterance-length capacity — users often fail not at grammar but at holding longer phrases in memory while speaking. Progressive expansion (backchaining) is a well-known ELT technique not yet represented in the app.",
  "files_to_modify": ["app/routers/elastic_sentence.py", "app/dal/elastic_sentence.py", "app/database.py", "app/main.py", "frontend/src/pages/ElasticSentencePage.tsx"],
  "priority": "high",
  "estimated_complexity": "medium"
}
